<div class="quiz-section">
  <h4 class="quiz-section_title">Check Your Understanding</h4>
  <p class="quiz-section_intro">See if you caught the key points from this stage.</p>

  <div id="quizCarouselS3" class="carousel slide quiz-carousel" data-bs-interval="false" data-bs-wrap="false" data-bs-touch="true" data-total="5">

    <!-- Indicators -->
    <div class="carousel-indicators quiz-dots">
      <button type="button" data-bs-target="#quizCarouselS3" data-bs-slide-to="0" class="quiz-dot active" aria-current="true"></button>
      <button type="button" data-bs-target="#quizCarouselS3" data-bs-slide-to="1" class="quiz-dot"></button>
      <button type="button" data-bs-target="#quizCarouselS3" data-bs-slide-to="2" class="quiz-dot"></button>
      <button type="button" data-bs-target="#quizCarouselS3" data-bs-slide-to="3" class="quiz-dot"></button>
      <button type="button" data-bs-target="#quizCarouselS3" data-bs-slide-to="4" class="quiz-dot"></button>
    </div>

    <div class="carousel-inner">

      <!-- Q1 -->
      <div class="carousel-item active">
        <div class="quiz-card">
          <p class="quiz-card_count">Question 1 of 5</p>
          <p class="quiz-card_question">How many IVF cycles does the Ontario Fertility Program (OFP) fund per eligible patient?</p>
          <div class="quiz-card_options">
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Unlimited</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Three</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Two</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">One</button>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-correct">
            ✓ <strong>Correct.</strong> The Ontario government funds one IVF cycle per eligible patient per lifetime through the OFP. Medications and additional services like genetic testing are typically not covered.
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-wrong">
            ✗ <strong>Not quite.</strong> The OFP covers one IVF cycle per eligible patient per lifetime. This is something many people are surprised to learn exists at all.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Q2 -->
      <div class="carousel-item">
        <div class="quiz-card">
          <p class="quiz-card_count">Question 2 of 5</p>
          <p class="quiz-card_question">Which statement about fertility treatment in Ontario is correct?</p>
          <div class="quiz-card_options">
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">IVF is the only fertility treatment available</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">Your doctor may recommend IUI, medication-only cycles, or lifestyle changes depending on your diagnosis</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">All fertility treatments are fully covered by OHIP</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">You must complete 6 IUI cycles before being eligible for IVF</button>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-correct">
            ✓ <strong>Correct.</strong> Treatment is not one-size-fits-all. Depending on your diagnosis, your doctor may recommend options other than IVF, including IUI, medication-only cycles, or lifestyle changes.
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-wrong">
            ✗ <strong>Not quite.</strong> IVF is not the only option. Depending on your diagnosis, your doctor may recommend IUI, medication-only cycles, or even lifestyle changes first. Treatment plans are personalized.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Q3 -->
      <div class="carousel-item">
        <div class="quiz-card">
          <p class="quiz-card_count">Question 3 of 5</p>
          <p class="quiz-card_question">What is covered under the Ontario Fertility Program (OFP) for IUI treatment?</p>
          <div class="quiz-card_options">
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Everything including medications and sperm washing</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">The insemination procedure, cycle monitoring, ultrasounds, and blood work</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Only the first three IUI cycles</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">IUI is not covered by the OFP</button>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-correct">
            ✓ <strong>Correct.</strong> The OFP covers the insemination procedure, cycle monitoring, ultrasounds, and blood work with no limit on the number of cycles. However, sperm washing and medications are not covered.
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-wrong">
            ✗ <strong>Not quite.</strong> IUI is funded by the OFP with no cycle limit, but only the procedure itself, monitoring, ultrasounds, and blood work are covered. Sperm washing and medications are out of pocket.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Q4 -->
      <div class="carousel-item">
        <div class="quiz-card">
          <p class="quiz-card_count">Question 4 of 5</p>
          <p class="quiz-card_question">What is the age requirement for OFP-funded IVF in Ontario?</p>
          <div class="quiz-card_options">
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Under 40</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">Under 45</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">Under 43</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">There is no age limit</button>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-correct">
            ✓ <strong>Correct.</strong> You must be under the age of 43 with a valid OHIP card to be eligible for one OFP-funded IVF cycle. Patients over 43 can still access IVF privately at their own cost.
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-wrong">
            ✗ <strong>Not quite.</strong> The OFP requires patients to be under 43 to qualify for a funded IVF cycle. There is no age restriction for privately funded IVF.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Q5 -->
      <div class="carousel-item">
        <div class="quiz-card">
          <p class="quiz-card_count">Question 5 of 5</p>
          <p class="quiz-card_question">How much can Ontario residents claim through the Ontario Fertility Treatment Tax Credit per year?</p>
          <div class="quiz-card_options">
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">50% of expenses, up to $10,000</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">100% of all fertility-related costs</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="true">25% of eligible expenses, up to $5,000</button>
            <button class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">A flat $2,500 reimbursement</button>
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-correct">
            ✓ <strong>Correct.</strong> Starting January 1, 2025, Ontario residents can claim a refundable tax credit of 25% on eligible fertility treatment expenses, up to a maximum of $5,000 per year.
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-card_feedback quiz-card_feedback-wrong">
            ✗ <strong>Not quite.</strong> The Ontario Fertility Treatment Tax Credit is 25% of eligible expenses, up to $5,000 per year. It is a refundable credit, meaning you receive the amount even if you owe no tax.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


    </div>

